I’m a massive supernerd and when @apple asked me to come to Cupertino for the launch of the iPhone15 I pinched myself.

As @becksworks shared her moodboards for motion and stills we asked ourselves - how far could we push the limits of studio stills and motion with an iPhone? Could I really execute a full photo and video editorial using lighting techniques that I normally use with “traditional” cameras (think front “curtain” flash sync with “shutter” drag – something we like to call “wudgies”)? 

A whirlwind 48 bi-coastal hours later I was back in my NYC studio and making literal magic with the iPhone15 Pro, iPhone15 Pro Max, and an incredible team of artists. 

I’m beyond grateful to the team that made it happen - and all in a super accelerated timeline. Thank you!
